\f2\fs48 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 
\f0\b\fs64 Intensity Panning
\f2\b0\fs48 \uc0\u8232 
\f1\fs36 using multichannel speakers can simulate azimuth cues for positioning of sounds between the speakers. A movement maintaining constant distance requires 
\f0\b sinusoidal
\f1\b0 , not linear, control functions. If linear amplitude change is used for intensity panning, a "hole in the middle" results because the sound intensity is proportional to the square of amplitude, and [1/2]
\fs30 \super  2
